A couple of months ago, seals were born on floating ice. With the changing season and currents, they have been drifting on the sea in the past days. Can they survive without the protection of parents? Watch the video to find out. About 'Journeys in Nature': Fauna in Liaodong Bay Series With a coastline stretching over 1,200 kilometers, Liaodong Bay, the northernmost bay in China, is covered in thick ice from winter to early spring, but remains full of life. This series explores the animal species inhabiting the bay, and their unique ways of surviving. For more: Fauna in Liaodong Bay Series | Ep. 1: A red paradise Fauna in Liaodong Bay Series | Ep. 2: Dancers on the red beach Fauna in Liaodong Bay Series | Ep. 3: Cornucopia of the sea Fauna in Liaodong Bay Series | Ep. 4: Saunders's gulls Fauna in Liaodong Bay Series | Ep. 5: Spotted seal (Cover image via screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)